The aroma of coffee and catered snacks spreads from the lounge, and a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit as career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops. Career counselors remind attendees to maintain eye contact, and camera crews from the university media team capture interviews, documenting the event. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom.

At the entrance, event staff scan registrations and hand out lanyards. Camera crews from the university media team are capturing interviews, while international students queue for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. Students clutch resumes inside branded folders as the dean stops by to thank recruiters for their support. An alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews, and as the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names, with recruiters reminding students to follow up with personalized emails.
